1
00:00:21,541 --> 00:00:24,750
[ELDER] We wait as long as we
must until the samurai are here.

2
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:26,875
We're the ones who
know the rice. Not them.

3
00:00:26,958 --> 00:00:28,416
Remember that!

4
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:32,333
If we say we cannot harvest
the crop yet... then we cannot!

5
00:00:32,416 --> 00:00:33,416
Oh, sure...

6
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,791
She only ratted us
out to the enemy--

7
00:00:34,875 --> 00:00:36,208
why would we blame
her for that?

8
00:00:36,291 --> 00:00:38,833
Tell us what you told them.

9
00:00:38,916 --> 00:00:41,875
I told them you were headed
to Kanna village after this.

10
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:43,875
You told them what?!

11
00:00:43,958 --> 00:00:45,708
[HYOGO] Kyuzo!

12
00:00:50,541 --> 00:00:54,541
Why... Kyuzo...? Why did you...

13
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:59,000
Because... I wanted to live.

14
00:01:01,125 --> 00:01:03,666
You're a hopeless fool.

15
00:01:05,583 --> 00:01:07,416
May I ask you
to come with us?

16
00:01:07,500 --> 00:01:08,625
When do we leave?

17
00:01:08,708 --> 00:01:09,750
Immediately.

18
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:12,041
That man is our enemy.

19
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:24,000
♪ opening song ♪

20
00:02:59,916 --> 00:03:01,208
[GOROBEI]
A three-way split.

21
00:03:01,291 --> 00:03:03,291
That's a bold move, old man.

22
00:03:03,375 --> 00:03:04,916
[HEIHACHI]
Big groups attract attention.

23
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,708
We'll have a better
shot this way.

24
00:03:06,791 --> 00:03:08,083
[KAMBEI]
That's my hope.

25
00:03:08,166 --> 00:03:10,666
The Nobuseri know too
much about us now.

26
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:13,916
We must play against their
expectation however we can.

27
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,375
Now, we'll need a rally
point, near the village.

28
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:17,958
Any suggestions?

29
00:03:18,041 --> 00:03:20,583
[KIRARA] There's Wing Rock,
on the way to the bridge.

30
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:21,750
[KATSUSHIRO] Wing Rock?

31
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:23,166
[KIRARA] It's an old boulder

32
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:24,791
that's been weathered down
into the shape of a wing.

33
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:26,583
It's impossible to miss.

34
00:03:26,666 --> 00:03:30,791
[KOMACHI] When me and my friends
go play, that's our secret base!

35
00:03:30,875 --> 00:03:32,791
[KAMBEI]
Well, that settles it, then.

36
00:03:32,875 --> 00:03:34,500
[SHICHIROJI]
So, how should we split up?

37
00:03:34,583 --> 00:03:35,916
[KAMBEI]
One farmer per group.

38
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,750
They know the land,
and can guide us.

39
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:40,458
Two samurai go with each.
Katsushiro, you're with me.

40
00:03:40,541 --> 00:03:41,875
[GOROBEI] Great.
I'll take the woodchopper.

41
00:03:41,958 --> 00:03:42,791
[SHICHIROJI] That'll work.

42
00:03:42,875 --> 00:03:44,333
[KAMBEI]
Then it's decided.

43
00:03:44,416 --> 00:03:47,416
We'll walk three paths, and
converge near the village soon.

44
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:49,083
Fortune be with you all.

45
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:50,791
[KIKUCHIYO]
Wait! You forgot me!

46
00:03:50,875 --> 00:03:52,125
Who do I go with?

47
00:03:52,208 --> 00:03:53,875
[KAMBEI]
That is not my concern.

48
00:03:53,958 --> 00:03:55,500
[KIKUCHIYO] Oh, I see!

49
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:59,208
Fine, then I'll just
go wherever I want!

50
00:04:12,208 --> 00:04:13,791
My divining
impulse was right.

51
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:15,291
This underground
water system

52
00:04:15,375 --> 00:04:17,750
will lead us all the way
back to Kanna from here.

53
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,583
Kyuzo-dono!

54
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:22,500
Why don't you
slow down a bit?

55
00:04:22,583 --> 00:04:25,166
We've got a
lady with us.

56
00:04:25,250 --> 00:04:27,375
I don't need considerations,
Great Samurai.

57
00:04:27,458 --> 00:04:30,291
I'm capable of walking fast.

58
00:04:40,791 --> 00:04:43,666
Sensei, may I ask what your
reasoning was for putting

59
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:45,791
Lady Kirara in the
group with Kyuzo-dono,

60
00:04:45,875 --> 00:04:47,500
despite her concerns about him?

61
00:04:47,583 --> 00:04:49,041
[KAMBEI]
The only reason that matters.

62
00:04:49,125 --> 00:04:51,708
Getting everyone to
the village alive.

63
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,083
What's the matter?
You worried 'cause

64
00:04:53,166 --> 00:04:55,125
sis should have you there
to protect her instead?

65
00:04:55,208 --> 00:04:58,291
No... it's nothing like
that... I mean I just...

66
00:04:58,375 --> 00:05:02,041
Sensei! It's awfully quiet
without Kikuchiyo-dono around,

67
00:05:02,125 --> 00:05:03,291
don't you think?

68
00:05:03,375 --> 00:05:04,583
[KAMBEI] Think we lack
something without him?

69
00:05:04,666 --> 00:05:06,208
Mm-Hmm.

70
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:14,458
[RUSTLING]

71
00:05:16,541 --> 00:05:17,875
[KOMACHI YELLS]

72
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:19,500
[KIKUCHIYO LAUGHS]

73
00:05:19,583 --> 00:05:20,958
[KIKUCHIYO] I gotcha...!

74
00:05:21,041 --> 00:05:23,208
Oh, hey! What do ya know...

75
00:05:23,291 --> 00:05:24,625
Kiku, it's you!

76
00:05:24,708 --> 00:05:27,041
So, you couldn't help
but follow me after all!

77
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:28,916
[KIKUCHIYO]
Follow? You've gone mad.

78
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,791
You just happened to
be walking in front of me.

79
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:33,666
Sure, sure, okay...
whatever makes you feel better.

80
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:36,166
[KIKUCHIYO]
No, well, look...

81
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:42,333
[GOROBEI] To hide a tree,
put it in a forest.

82
00:05:42,416 --> 00:05:44,791
To hide a person, go into town.

83
00:05:44,875 --> 00:05:46,916
The main road is the most
obvious route to Kanna--

84
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,333
and the last they'd
expect us to take.

85
00:05:49,416 --> 00:05:50,875
Blend in by
standing out.

86
00:05:50,958 --> 00:05:52,791
But aren't these outfits
kind of pushing it?

87
00:05:52,875 --> 00:05:55,250
I really don't feel very
comfortable with this...

88
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:57,541
Come on, man!
Comfort is for the stagnant.

89
00:05:57,625 --> 00:05:59,208
If anyone asks, just tell them,

90
00:05:59,291 --> 00:06:01,375
"We are a traveling
troupe of merry men,

91
00:06:01,458 --> 00:06:03,416
with a hearty joke
and a joyful song!"

92
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:04,916
And you have to
say it like that.

93
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,666
But I can't... I'm just
a farmer, rice is all I know.

94
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:10,041
I don't know
how to perform.

95
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:12,458
Of course not...!
None of us do...!

96
00:06:12,541 --> 00:06:14,166
But the point is
you're not you anymore,

97
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:17,416
you're the Sickle Master!
Maguso Koedayu.

98
00:06:17,500 --> 00:06:20,083
And I'll be the man who breaks
blocks to break his bread!

99
00:06:20,166 --> 00:06:22,958
Woodchopping Master,
Hoho Eminosuke.

100
00:06:23,041 --> 00:06:25,625
Y'know...?
The name kinda suits you!

101
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:28,458
[GOROBEI AND HEIHACHI LAUGH]

102
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:32,750
We shouldn't be laughing.
This is life or death.

103
00:06:32,833 --> 00:06:34,958
We're laughing because
it's life or death...

104
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:38,916
It's Gorobei-dono's style...
You should try it out.

105
00:06:43,666 --> 00:06:45,583
[RIKICHI SIGHS]

106
00:06:53,500 --> 00:06:57,333
[KIRARA BREATHES HEAVILY]

107
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:59,666
Those are our
neighbors down there.

108
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:03,500
Kanna Village is not
very far beyond them.

109
00:07:03,583 --> 00:07:07,000
It's a difficult climb, Lady
Kirara--you're out of breath.

110
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:10,375
Why don't we take a break here,
at least for a few minutes.

111
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:20,541
No thanks... We can rest
when we get there...

112
00:07:20,625 --> 00:07:22,500
My people are waiting for us.

113
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:24,333
They need me.

114
00:07:24,416 --> 00:07:25,625
And I thought your
motivation was

115
00:07:25,708 --> 00:07:28,208
getting away from
Kyuzo-dono here.

116
00:07:28,291 --> 00:07:31,041
I'm not going to pretend that
I like him, Great Samurai.

117
00:07:31,125 --> 00:07:32,666
I honestly can't tell
what he's thinking,

118
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:34,750
and I don't trust
men like that...

119
00:07:34,833 --> 00:07:38,375
He told Kambei he wanted to kill
him--doesn't that bother you?

120
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,875
I don't know...

121
00:07:40,958 --> 00:07:42,125
[KYUZO] Scouts.

122
00:07:42,208 --> 00:07:44,000
[SHICHIROJI]
No, don't look.

123
00:07:47,416 --> 00:07:49,750
Give me your foot.
Like I'm your servant.

124
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:51,500
Just do it.

125
00:07:53,666 --> 00:07:54,666
[SCOUT 1] Is it them?

126
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:57,000
[SCOUT 2]
No. The numbers are wrong.

127
00:07:57,083 --> 00:07:59,916
[SCOUT 1] They may have
split up. Let's kill them.

128
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,416
[SCOUT 2] Let's observe.

129
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:03,125
They may not be
the ones we want.

130
00:08:03,208 --> 00:08:05,500
We don't need an incident.

131
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:09,541
Wanna start a fight?

132
00:08:12,166 --> 00:08:14,916
Great Samurai, please don't...
I'm begging you...

133
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,958
You'd only put us at risk for
a fight that could be avoided.

134
00:08:18,041 --> 00:08:20,541
Getting to the village
should be our top priority.

135
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:24,291
Let's not take lives
when we don't need to.

136
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:46,125
♪ He's still thinking of Sister.
He's still thinking of Sister! ♪

137
00:08:46,208 --> 00:08:47,708
Would you please
stop with that?

138
00:08:47,791 --> 00:08:49,375
Oh, you can try to hide it...

139
00:08:49,458 --> 00:08:54,333
But... I can tell that you are
totally in love with her!

140
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:56,333
[KATSUSHIRO LAUGHS]

141
00:08:56,416 --> 00:08:58,041
[KATSUSHIRO] I think you
might be right, sprout!

142
00:08:58,125 --> 00:08:59,875
Look at him blush! Heh.

143
00:08:59,958 --> 00:09:02,208
Laugh all you want...
It's not true...

144
00:09:02,291 --> 00:09:03,791
I took an oath, all right?

145
00:09:03,875 --> 00:09:06,916
I swore I'd protect her, that's
all I'm thinking about--Period!

146
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:09,583
[KATSUSHIRO] Ohh... 
Look how mad he's getting!

147
00:09:09,666 --> 00:09:12,250
Pretty obvious now! 
Hah, hah, ha, ha!

148
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:13,416
I don't know, though.

149
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:15,833
Are samurai even
allowed to fall in love?

150
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,541
No one's falling
into anything, okay?!

151
00:09:17,625 --> 00:09:19,375
I told you,
it's not like that!

152
00:09:19,458 --> 00:09:20,958
You've lost this battle.

153
00:09:21,041 --> 00:09:22,416
[KATSUSHIRO SIGHS]

154
00:09:23,541 --> 00:09:28,833
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

155
00:09:32,291 --> 00:09:35,250
Hey! Wash your troubles
away with some fun!

156
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:37,041
The show's about to start!

157
00:09:37,125 --> 00:09:40,875
In three...! Two...! One!

158
00:09:47,041 --> 00:09:49,291
[TROUPE GIRL 1]
Wow! Great extension!

159
00:09:49,375 --> 00:09:51,916
She's really feeling it today!

160
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,833
Now here comes the finale!

161
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:12,583
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

162
00:10:12,666 --> 00:10:14,333
Well done! Most inspired!

163
00:10:14,416 --> 00:10:16,625
That's one
hell of a trick.

164
00:10:23,916 --> 00:10:27,083
[TROUPE GIRLS LAUGH]

165
00:10:27,166 --> 00:10:29,708
Thanks and come again!

166
00:10:42,708 --> 00:10:43,875
[KOMACHI]
You still mad at us?

167
00:10:43,958 --> 00:10:45,125
[KATSUSHIRO]
I'm not mad.

168
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:47,166
I'm nothing. I'm just
watching the stream.

169
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:48,333
[KOMACHI]
If you're not mad,

170
00:10:48,416 --> 00:10:50,041
how come you're off
sitting by yourself?

171
00:10:50,125 --> 00:10:52,625
[KATSUSHIRO]
I-I'm just thinking.

172
00:10:52,708 --> 00:10:54,375
[KIKUCHIYO]
You're a samurai, aren't ya?

173
00:10:54,458 --> 00:10:56,791
How 'bout a little less thinkin'
and a little more doin'?!

174
00:10:56,875 --> 00:10:58,750
Ladies never go
for the shy guys!

175
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:00,166
Look, we've
been through this!

176
00:11:00,250 --> 00:11:02,583
Yeah, making her like
you might be tough...

177
00:11:02,666 --> 00:11:05,458
Sis did say you don't
smell like battle, after all...

178
00:11:05,541 --> 00:11:07,458
[KIKUCHIYO]
Oh yeah, you're screwed.

179
00:11:07,541 --> 00:11:08,791
Since you won't drop it,

180
00:11:08,875 --> 00:11:10,750
why don't you tell me what
the smell of battle is?

181
00:11:10,833 --> 00:11:12,583
I don't know,
I'm just a kid...

182
00:11:12,666 --> 00:11:16,041
But I bet Kiku can tell you
exactly what it is, right?

183
00:11:16,125 --> 00:11:18,625
[KIKUCHIYO]
Huh? Oh, sure, of course.

184
00:11:18,708 --> 00:11:23,875
Blood, grease, swords, you know,
some body odor. Macho stuff!

185
00:11:23,958 --> 00:11:25,541
[KAMBEI LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

186
00:11:25,625 --> 00:11:28,541
But anyway, that's not what you
should be worrying about, kid.

187
00:11:28,625 --> 00:11:29,875
[KATSUSHIRO] No?

188
00:11:29,958 --> 00:11:31,333
[KIKUCHIYO] Just think
who she's with right now.

189
00:11:31,416 --> 00:11:33,666
There's Master Two-swords,
with the whole mysterious,

190
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:36,791
tough-man loner thing
girls go crazy for...

191
00:11:36,875 --> 00:11:38,208
And then there's Momotaro,

192
00:11:38,291 --> 00:11:41,833
who we already know is
a romancer! Competition!

193
00:11:41,916 --> 00:11:45,125
And Sister isn't
getting any younger!

194
00:11:45,208 --> 00:11:46,500
That's ridiculous.

195
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:47,833
[KIKUCHIYO]
Sure! You say that now!

196
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:49,000
By the time we
reach the village,

197
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,500
it'll prob'ly be too late!

198
00:11:50,583 --> 00:11:52,375
[KATSUSHIRO]
Can we just drop it?!

199
00:11:53,666 --> 00:11:55,708
Katsushiro... Tell me...

200
00:11:55,791 --> 00:11:58,291
Why did you want
to become a samurai?

201
00:12:02,791 --> 00:12:04,500
[SHICHIROJI]
Decisions, decisions...

202
00:12:04,583 --> 00:12:06,083
Which way to go?

203
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:10,708
The underground channel flows
beneath both of these paths.

204
00:12:10,791 --> 00:12:14,125
Either way should lead us
directly to Kanna Village.

205
00:12:14,208 --> 00:12:15,291
Excuse me?

206
00:12:15,375 --> 00:12:17,750
Easy now... Let's just
go where he wants.

207
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:19,625
[KIRARA] He chooses
for us, in silence,

208
00:12:19,708 --> 00:12:21,208
and expects us to follow?

209
00:12:21,291 --> 00:12:24,375
Any hope I had of understanding
this man is quickly fading...

210
00:12:24,458 --> 00:12:25,666
Let me say it again--

211
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:28,666
I'm strongly against
him coming to my village.

212
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:31,541
A samurai should be judged by
his actions, Water Priestess,

213
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:32,708
not by his words.

214
00:12:32,791 --> 00:12:34,333
Well sometimes
words are needed--

215
00:12:34,416 --> 00:12:37,208
you can't convey
everything with a stare.

216
00:12:38,541 --> 00:12:39,541
[KIRARA GASPS]

217
00:12:40,708 --> 00:12:42,208
They're back.

218
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:40,666
No offense... But you'd
better sit this one out--

219
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:42,875
behind those rocks
would be nice.

220
00:14:20,583 --> 00:14:22,375
[KIRARA YELLS]

221
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:35,416
[KYUZO GRUNTS]

222
00:14:48,875 --> 00:14:50,666
You're hurt...

223
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:53,375
You knew they'd come
back eventually...

224
00:14:53,458 --> 00:14:56,083
It's why you wanted
to fight before...

225
00:14:57,958 --> 00:15:01,916
That was your line
of reasoning, wasn't it?

226
00:15:10,583 --> 00:15:11,666
[KATSUSHIRO] Sensei...

227
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:13,875
You asked me why I
wanted to be a samurai,

228
00:15:13,958 --> 00:15:16,875
but does one really
need a reason?

229
00:15:16,958 --> 00:15:18,958
[KAMBEI] You don't know?

230
00:15:22,083 --> 00:15:24,208
[RIKICHI]
Stop it, please!

231
00:15:24,291 --> 00:15:27,875
Why are you doing this
to me? What did I do?

232
00:15:27,958 --> 00:15:30,916
[TROUPE GIRL 3] Relax. You won't
pull it off with hairy legs.

233
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:31,916
What?

234
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,083
Enjoy it!

235
00:15:33,166 --> 00:15:35,125
Your skin will feel
better, all smooth!

236
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:38,750
But... why...?
Great Samurai!

237
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:39,958
Lower your voice!

238
00:15:40,041 --> 00:15:42,083
Or do you want us to
be caught and gutted?

239
00:15:42,166 --> 00:15:43,333
No...

240
00:15:43,416 --> 00:15:45,541
Now you are making
me beautiful, aren't you?

241
00:15:45,625 --> 00:15:46,875
Oh, naturally...

242
00:15:46,958 --> 00:15:49,375
Though you won't be as
lovely as Eminosuke, here!

243
00:15:49,458 --> 00:15:50,625
[RIKICHI SOBS]

244
00:15:50,708 --> 00:15:53,708
We're doomed...! The two
of you have gone insane!

245
00:15:53,791 --> 00:15:55,000
All right...

246
00:15:55,083 --> 00:15:57,541
That's almost done.
I'll start on his clothes.

247
00:15:57,625 --> 00:15:58,958
[RIKICHI SOBS]

248
00:16:08,291 --> 00:16:10,458
[KIRARA]
Great Kyuzo...

249
00:16:10,541 --> 00:16:12,541
Before we reach
Kanna, I must know--

250
00:16:12,625 --> 00:16:15,791
why do you wish to fight
Kambei? What did he do?

251
00:16:15,875 --> 00:16:18,708
He's samurai...
That's all.

252
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:27,375
Sensei...

253
00:16:30,291 --> 00:16:32,625
[KATSUSHIRO]
Sensei, the first day I met you,

254
00:16:32,708 --> 00:16:35,083
I said I wanted to be a
samurai for the mindset,

255
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:36,833
always ready for war.

256
00:16:36,916 --> 00:16:38,833
But after being with
you, and the others,

257
00:16:38,916 --> 00:16:40,166
I have my doubts.

258
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:42,375
Maybe that reason
isn't good enough.

259
00:16:42,458 --> 00:16:43,875
[KIKUCHIYO]
Samurai have it too easy!

260
00:16:43,958 --> 00:16:46,541
Don't have to work,
too much time to think!

261
00:16:46,625 --> 00:16:49,125
"Is my reason good?
How am I feeling today?

262
00:16:49,208 --> 00:16:50,291
What does it mean?!"

263
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:52,833
A whole bunch of
crap if you ask me.

264
00:16:52,916 --> 00:16:54,833
[KAMBEI]
Katsushiro...

265
00:16:54,916 --> 00:16:57,541
When you were hurt by that
arrow in the Guardians' cave,

266
00:16:57,625 --> 00:16:59,875
what went through your mind?

267
00:16:59,958 --> 00:17:01,416
Let's see...

268
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,791
Well, I was thinking about what
would happen to everybody...

269
00:17:03,875 --> 00:17:06,000
...to Lady Kirara
and then...

270
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:08,791
...to the entire village of
Kanna that we swore to protect.

271
00:17:08,875 --> 00:17:13,375
[KAMBEI] Sometimes we only see
clearly through a lens of pain.

272
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:19,125
Huh? I didn't follow that...

273
00:17:19,208 --> 00:17:21,500
Did you get what
he was saying, Kiku?

274
00:17:21,583 --> 00:17:22,541
He talks funny.

275
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:24,083
[KIKUCHIYO] Who cares?!

276
00:17:24,166 --> 00:17:27,916
Oh, good... That means
we can be clueless together!

277
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,750
[TROUPE GIRL 1]
Take care now, "ladies!"

278
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:31,583
[TROUPE GIRL 3]
Come see us again!

279
00:17:31,666 --> 00:17:34,125
Why me...? I've never
been so embarrassed.

280
00:17:34,208 --> 00:17:36,000
Why couldn't I be
with the normal ones?

281
00:17:36,083 --> 00:17:37,541
[GOROBEI]
Come on, man! You're stunning.

282
00:17:37,625 --> 00:17:40,333
[HEIHACHI] I didn't know
you had such nice legs.

283
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,125
Gorobei-dono,
looks like trouble.

284
00:17:53,666 --> 00:17:55,958
[RIKICHI] This is the
Bandits' work, I'm sure of it!

285
00:17:56,041 --> 00:17:57,625
Another village wiped out!

286
00:17:57,708 --> 00:18:01,708
[GOROBEI] Fresh smoke.
They're still close.

287
00:18:01,791 --> 00:18:03,708
Here we go...

288
00:18:05,583 --> 00:18:09,000
[BANDIT 1] Travelers.
Explain your presence.

289
00:18:09,083 --> 00:18:10,458
Ahh...!

290
00:18:10,541 --> 00:18:12,541
Don't pinch me, girls,
I don't want to wake up!

291
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:14,208
It's the real Nobuseri!

292
00:18:14,291 --> 00:18:16,875
Wow... I can't tell you
how big a fan I am!

293
00:18:16,958 --> 00:18:20,083
Your work is absolutely divine!

294
00:18:20,166 --> 00:18:22,000
[HEIHACHI]
How brutishly handsome!

295
00:18:22,083 --> 00:18:24,250
The strong chest,
the booming voice.

296
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:26,291
Oh, I think
I'm falling in love!

297
00:18:26,375 --> 00:18:27,958
[BANDIT 2]
Oh, they're prostitutes.

298
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:30,041
Us...?! No, nothing of the sort!

299
00:18:30,125 --> 00:18:31,333
[GOROBEI]
We're entertainers,

300
00:18:31,416 --> 00:18:33,916
the merriest troupe
this side of the capital!

301
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,250
[GOROBEI GIGGLES]

302
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:36,666
[HEIHACHI GIGGLES]

303
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:38,208
[RIKICHI GIGGLES]

304
00:18:41,833 --> 00:18:43,791
[BANDIT 1]
You there. Crawler...

305
00:18:43,875 --> 00:18:46,000
Tell us your name.

306
00:18:47,875 --> 00:18:50,791
I'm a... Ma-Ma--
Ma-Ma-Ma-Ma-Maguso.

307
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:54,000
[BANDIT 1] Ma-Ma--
Ma-Ma-Maguso, eh? Heh, heh.

308
00:18:54,083 --> 00:18:55,833
Haven't heard that one before...

309
00:18:55,916 --> 00:18:57,541
You seem shy for a performer.

310
00:18:57,625 --> 00:19:00,333
How do I know you're not
a fugitive in disguise?

311
00:19:00,416 --> 00:19:03,333
[GOROBEI] Oh, cut it out!
You Bandie-wandies are too much!

312
00:19:03,416 --> 00:19:05,541
[BANDIT 1] Then I suppose
you ladies wouldn't mind

313
00:19:05,625 --> 00:19:08,750
giving us a little
taste of your act...

314
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:10,250
No?

315
00:19:10,333 --> 00:19:15,375
Last chance... Perform for us
now or we take your heads!

316
00:19:15,458 --> 00:19:16,291
Shall we?

317
00:19:16,375 --> 00:19:18,333
Don't see
much of a choice.

318
00:19:20,625 --> 00:19:23,041
[RIKICHI] Oohhh!
Nobuseri, you're so dreamy!

319
00:19:23,125 --> 00:19:25,291
You had Maguso
nervous from love!

320
00:19:25,375 --> 00:19:26,541
[RIKICHI GIGGLES]

321
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:29,333
Sure I'll dance for you!

322
00:19:29,416 --> 00:19:31,791
Okay!

323
00:19:31,875 --> 00:19:34,833
♪ Need to plant the rice,
and harvest it by night! ♪

324
00:19:34,916 --> 00:19:38,083
♪ The rice bran on my skin
makes it feel so nice! ♪

325
00:19:38,166 --> 00:19:41,250
♪ The sun tans my face,
and the sweat makes it smooth! ♪

326
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:45,041
♪ And bending down in the fields
makes my bottom strong, too! ♪

327
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:47,833
♪ A-doo-doo-doo! Doodly-doo! ♪

328
00:19:47,916 --> 00:19:50,666
♪ Everywhere you look,
my skin is silky soft... ♪

329
00:19:50,750 --> 00:19:53,083
♪ Peek under my dress!
Here! Let me take it off! ♪

330
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:55,583
[BANDIT 1] Uhh...

331
00:19:55,666 --> 00:19:57,041
[HEIHACHI LAUGHS LIGHTLY]

332
00:19:57,125 --> 00:19:58,833
[GOROBEI] Uh...

333
00:19:58,916 --> 00:20:01,041
[RIKICHI GIGGLES]

334
00:20:01,125 --> 00:20:03,750
[BANDIT 2] That's quite
enough, ma'am really.

335
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:07,333
Just, put your dress
back down please. Ugh...

336
00:20:11,708 --> 00:20:13,166
[HEIHACHI AND GOROBEI SIGH]

337
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:19,833
We owe you one...

338
00:20:19,916 --> 00:20:22,833
Thanks to your bravery,
we avoided a fight.

339
00:20:22,916 --> 00:20:25,083
[RIKICHI] But...
I mean we could have...

340
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:28,583
[GOROBEI] Easy, man. You don't
want your makeup to run.

341
00:20:32,291 --> 00:20:36,416
[GROUP LAUGHS]

342
00:20:46,250 --> 00:20:48,083
[MANZO] Elder, please!

343
00:20:48,166 --> 00:20:50,375
I stayed awake all
night thinking about it...

344
00:20:50,458 --> 00:20:54,083
Bringing the samurai here
is just too dangerous now!

345
00:20:54,166 --> 00:20:56,625
It seemed like that Bandit
patrol knew everything...

346
00:20:56,708 --> 00:20:59,166
The timing of it was
too exact to be a bluff.

347
00:20:59,250 --> 00:21:01,125
I'm sure they did know
we hired samurai,

348
00:21:01,208 --> 00:21:03,666
and they were giving us a chance
to save ourselves, Elder.

349
00:21:03,750 --> 00:21:05,583
We'd be fools not to take it!

350
00:21:05,666 --> 00:21:07,625
But how could they have
figured it out so quickly,

351
00:21:07,708 --> 00:21:09,458
before the samurai
even got here?

352
00:21:09,541 --> 00:21:11,458
You know they have
their fingers in everything,

353
00:21:11,541 --> 00:21:14,416
and Rikichi and Kirara probably
talked to dozens of samurai--

354
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:17,291
one of them must've
tipped the Bandits off!

355
00:21:17,375 --> 00:21:18,875
[VILLAGERS MURMUR]

356
00:21:18,958 --> 00:21:20,375
[ELDER SIGHS]

357
00:21:31,458 --> 00:21:32,958
[KATSUSHIRO]
So, this is Wing Rock?

358
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:34,666
I see where it gets the name.

359
00:21:34,750 --> 00:21:36,666
[KOMACHI] Yup, this is where
we're supposed to meet!

360
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,375
Isn't it pretty?

361
00:21:38,458 --> 00:21:40,708
I guess the others
haven't gotten here yet.

362
00:21:40,791 --> 00:21:42,291
What's the matter?

363
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:45,083
You're still worried about sis
with those other samurai, huh?

364
00:21:45,166 --> 00:21:46,791
[KATSUSHIRO]
For the last time, no!

365
00:21:46,875 --> 00:21:49,583
[GOROBEI]
Ladies and gentlemen...

366
00:21:49,666 --> 00:21:52,125
The Troupe of Merry
Travelers has arrived!

367
00:21:52,208 --> 00:21:53,166
Ta-da!

368
00:21:53,250 --> 00:21:54,500
[RIKICHI SOBS]

369
00:21:54,583 --> 00:21:56,041
[KAMBEI] Uh...

370
00:21:56,125 --> 00:21:58,541
[KIKUCHIYO]
Hey, you guys look pretty good!

371
00:21:58,625 --> 00:21:59,958
Um, no offense Kiku...

372
00:22:00,041 --> 00:22:02,166
But I don't think you
have very good taste.

373
00:22:02,250 --> 00:22:04,208
[KAMBEI] Looks like your
journey was a strange one.

374
00:22:04,291 --> 00:22:05,750
But I'm glad you're safe.

375
00:22:05,833 --> 00:22:07,708
[GOROBEI] Any word on
the third group yet?

376
00:22:07,791 --> 00:22:09,125
[KAMBEI GRUNTS]

377
00:22:09,208 --> 00:22:11,875
Bandits are in the area--
we had a run-in ourselves.

378
00:22:11,958 --> 00:22:14,625
[KATSUSHIRO] Sensei, 
I can go look for them.

379
00:22:14,708 --> 00:22:16,041
I'll be careful.

380
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:21,666
Shichiroji-dono.
Where are the others?

381
00:22:21,750 --> 00:22:24,333
Well, we made it to the rock
a little ahead of schedule.

382
00:22:24,416 --> 00:22:26,291
So uh...

383
00:22:31,333 --> 00:22:33,583
[KIKUCHIYO LAUGHS]

384
00:22:39,416 --> 00:22:40,916
[KIRARA] All done.

385
00:22:44,750 --> 00:22:47,750
Thank you saving my
life, Great Samurai.

386
00:22:47,833 --> 00:22:50,166
Thanks for the stitch.

387
00:22:53,916 --> 00:22:56,875
I'd say our
journey went well.

388
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:01,625
Yeah, I guess so.

389
00:23:01,708 --> 00:23:03,791
[KIKUCHIYO]
Come on, we got work to do.

390
00:23:13,416 --> 00:23:18,375
♪ closing song ♪

391
00:25:24,791 --> 00:25:25,916
[KOMACHI]
Dear Okara,

392
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:27,708
Today we made the final
trek to the village,

393
00:25:27,791 --> 00:25:29,750
which means I should
see you real soon!

394
00:25:29,833 --> 00:25:31,166
We split up in groups,

395
00:25:31,250 --> 00:25:33,583
and I got to be the guide
for Kambe and Katsushiro.

396
00:25:33,666 --> 00:25:35,708
Then guess who showed up? Kiku!

397
00:25:35,791 --> 00:25:38,000
He says he wasn't following me,
but I know better. 

398
00:25:38,083 --> 00:25:40,458
He can't live without
his smart sidekick!

399
00:25:40,541 --> 00:25:42,708
We had lots of fun
teasing Katsushiro,

400
00:25:42,791 --> 00:25:45,375
because I know he likes sis,
but he won't admit it.

401
00:25:45,458 --> 00:25:46,833
And we made him jealous

402
00:25:46,916 --> 00:25:49,125
'cause she was in the group
with the two new samurai,

403
00:25:49,208 --> 00:25:51,875
and they're both tough and
smell like battle a bunch I bet,

404
00:25:51,958 --> 00:25:53,583
which you know sis likes.

405
00:25:53,666 --> 00:25:56,125
Then again, she
doesn't trust Kyuzo at all, 

406
00:25:56,208 --> 00:25:57,750
and doesn't think he
should be in the group,

407
00:25:57,833 --> 00:26:00,666
so maybe Katsushiro
has a chance after all. 

408
00:26:00,750 --> 00:26:02,833
I don't what will happen
with those two, honestly.

409
00:26:02,916 --> 00:26:04,750
He wants to protect
her real bad,

410
00:26:04,833 --> 00:26:06,500
and prove he's a brave samurai,

411
00:26:06,583 --> 00:26:09,000
but not even he knows
if he has it in him.

412
00:26:09,083 --> 00:26:10,166
What do you think makes it so

413
00:26:10,250 --> 00:26:12,666
some people can be
heroes and others can't?

414
00:26:12,750 --> 00:26:14,458
We'll talk about that
when I see you...

415
00:26:14,541 --> 00:26:16,625
I can't wait! Bye-bye!

